.TH MUSIC "1" "December 2025" "music 202208131717-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
music \- Music player launcher script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B music
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B music
is a script for launching and playing music. It provides a simple interface to start music playback using available music players on the system.
.PP
The script detects available music players and uses the appropriate one for playback.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Set the working directory for music files
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B music
Launch the music player
.TP
.B music --dir ~/Music
Play music from the specified directory
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/music/settings.conf
User configuration file for music preferences
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/music/
Log file directory for error tracking
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Opens in a terminal if not already running in one
.IP \(bu 2
Detects and uses available music players
.IP \(bu 2
Supports MPD-based playback
